		<demo key="reliableupload">
			<shortDescription>
				The application shows how to set up Image Uploader to make upload process stable in the case of problems with Internet connection.
			</shortDescription>
			<fullDescription>
				<p>
					Sometimes connection problems occur unexpectedly during uploading files to a Web server.
					This sample application demonstrates how to set up Image Uploader to recover the upload process.
					The approach requires Image Uploader to send each file by chunks in multiple HTTP POST requests.
					Also we specify how many attempts Image Uploader performs in order to resume upload of the current
					chunk and period of time between these attempts. Here are the key features used in the application:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Upload of files by chunks of fixed size in multiple HTTP POST requests.</li>
					<li>Resume upload automatically when connection breaks.</li>
					<li>
						Upload of MD5 hash values for selected files. This feature allows us to check
						whether files added to the upload list have already been uploaded to the Web server or not.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="license-description">
					This demo application works with <strong>Professional</strong>, <strong>Print</strong>, or
					<strong>Premium</strong> edition of Image Uploader.
				</p>
			</fullDescription>
